{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "a1b2c3d4-arkano-banking",
    "name": "Arkano - Plataforma bancaria (microservicios)",
    "description": "Colección para probar accounts (3001), transactions (3002) y ai (3003).\n\n**Orden:** carpeta **01 - Accounts** → **02 - Transactions** → **03 - AI**. Tras crear cuentas espera **1–3 s** (Kafka + snapshots). Tras cada `POST /transactions` haz **GET Transaction** en bucle hasta `completed` o `rejected`.\n\n**Variables:** esta colección usa *collection variables* (`clientId`, `accountId`, `transactionId`, …). Si importas el entorno `arkano-local`, las URLs pueden venir del entorno.\n\n**Respuestas:** envelope HTTP común `success`, `data`, `statusCode`, `timestamp`.\n\nDocumentación: `docs/05-test/pruebas-con-postman.md`",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "accountsUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3001" },
    { "key": "transactionsUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3002" },
    { "key": "aiUrl", "value": "http://localhost:3003" },
    { "key": "clientId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "clientId2", "value": "" },
    { "key": "accountId", "value": "" },
    { "key": "accountId2", "value": "" },
    { "key": "transactionId", "value": "" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "01 - Accounts",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Crear cliente (principal)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('Tiene clientId', () => {",
                  "  pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "  pm.expect(json.data.clientId).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.clientId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('clientId', json.data.clientId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Cliente Postman\",\n  \"email\": \"{{$guid}}@postman-test.local\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{accountsUrl}}/clients",
            "description": "Crea un cliente. Guarda `clientId` en variables de colección."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Crear cuenta (principal)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('clientId')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Ejecuta antes \"POST Crear cliente (principal)\"');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.accountId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accountId', json.data.accountId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"clientId\": \"{{clientId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{accountsUrl}}/accounts",
            "description": "Espera unos segundos después para que transactions sincronice el snapshot (Kafka)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Crear cliente (segundo - transferencias)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.clientId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('clientId2', json.data.clientId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Cliente Postman 2\",\n  \"email\": \"{{$guid}}@postman-test.local\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{accountsUrl}}/clients",
            "description": "Opcional: necesario para probar transferencia entre cuentas."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Crear cuenta (segunda)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('clientId2')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Ejecuta antes \"POST Crear cliente (segundo)\"');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.accountId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('accountId2', json.data.accountId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"clientId\": \"{{clientId2}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{accountsUrl}}/accounts",
            "description": "Cuenta destino para transferencias."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Cuenta por id (principal)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Envelope OK', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.accountId).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('accountId'));",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('balance');",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{accountsUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId}}",
            "description": "Consulta saldo de la cuenta principal. Requiere `accountId` (carpeta 01)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Cuenta por id (segunda)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('accountId2')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Ejecuta antes POST cuenta segunda o ignora este request');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Envelope OK', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.accountId).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('accountId2'));",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{accountsUrl}}/accounts/{{accountId2}}",
            "description": "Útil para validar saldo del destino tras una transferencia."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "02 - Transactions",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Depósito",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('accountId')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Completa antes la carpeta 01 - Accounts');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "pm.test('Pending', () => pm.expect(json.data.status).to.eql('pending'));",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.transactionId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', json.data.transactionId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"deposit\",\n  \"amount\": 100,\n  \"targetAccountId\": \"{{accountId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{transactionsUrl}}/transactions",
            "description": "Luego ejecuta GET Transaction varias veces hasta completed (o espera 1–2 s)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Transaction por id",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('transactionId')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Ejecuta antes un POST en esta carpeta');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Estado transacción', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.status).to.be.oneOf(['pending', 'completed', 'rejected']);",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.transactionId).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('transactionId'));",
                  "  });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{transactionsUrl}}/transactions/{{transactionId}}",
            "description": "Repite hasta `completed` o `rejected` (polling tras POST)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Retiro",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.transactionId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', json.data.transactionId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"withdrawal\",\n  \"amount\": 25,\n  \"sourceAccountId\": \"{{accountId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{transactionsUrl}}/transactions",
            "description": "Requiere saldo suficiente (haz depósito antes)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Transferencia",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('accountId2')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Crea la segunda cuenta en 01 - Accounts');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.transactionId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', json.data.transactionId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"transfer\",\n  \"amount\": 10,\n  \"sourceAccountId\": \"{{accountId}}\",\n  \"targetAccountId\": \"{{accountId2}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{transactionsUrl}}/transactions",
            "description": "Dos legs de TransactionCompleted; usa GET explanations tras completed."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST Retiro sin fondos (esperar rejected)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Status 202', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "if (json.data && json.data.transactionId) {",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('transactionId', json.data.transactionId);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"withdrawal\",\n  \"amount\": 999999999,\n  \"sourceAccountId\": \"{{accountId}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{transactionsUrl}}/transactions",
            "description": "Debería pasar a rejected. Luego GET Transaction y GET explanations."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 - AI",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET Explicaciones por transactionId",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('transactionId')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Ejecuta antes un POST en 02 - Transactions');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Explicaciones', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.transactionId).to.be.a('string');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.explanations).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.explanations.length).to.be.above(0);",
                  "  });",
                  "}",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 404) {",
                  "  pm.test('Aún sin explicación — reintenta tras Kafka/ai-service', () => true);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{aiUrl}}/explanations/{{transactionId}}",
            "description": "Cuando la transacción esté `completed` o `rejected` y ai-service haya consumido el evento. **404:** espera 1–3 s y reintenta."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET Resumen historial por cuenta",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (!pm.collectionVariables.get('accountId')) {",
                  "  throw new Error('Completa carpeta 01 - Accounts');",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.test('Resumen cuenta', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(json.success).to.be.true;",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data.accountId).to.eql(pm.collectionVariables.get('accountId'));",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('summary');",
                  "    pm.expect(json.data).to.have.property('provider');",
                  "  });",
                  "}",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 404) {",
                  "  pm.test('Sin filas con accountId aún — completa varios TransactionCompleted en esa cuenta', () => true);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{aiUrl}}/explanations/account/{{accountId}}/summary",
            "description": "Requiere explicaciones previas con `accountId` (p. ej. depósitos completados). `USE_OLLAMA=true` → Ollama; si no, mock. Ver `docs/07-team/guia-ollama-local.md`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
